    NLP for Social Good

    Click to edit text

    New Intiative

    Starting from ACL 2021

    Click to edit text

    NLP for Social Good (NLP4SG) is a new intiative (starting from ACL 2021) that encourages NLP researchers to associate NLP technologies with societal impacts. We have a list of events, resources, and discussion channels for all that are interested :)!

    Click to edit text

    I want to learn -- What is NLP4SG?

    I want to discuss! -- Join our Slack

    Good Resources on NLP4SG

    Click to edit text

    Events

    1. ACL 2021 -- Special Track "NLP for Social Good" [Register for ACL]

    2. ACL 2021 Workshop -- NLP for Positive Impact 2021 [Schedule (Aug 5)]

    3. ACL 2021 Meetup Event -- NLP for Social Good Meetup [Zoom link] [Time: TBD]

    What is NLP for Social Good?

    1. Curated GitHub paper list of NLP on Social Good

    2. "How Good Is NLP? A Sober Look at NLP Tasks through the Lens of Social Impact" (Findings of ACL 2021) by Zhijing Jin (Max Planck Institute&ETH), Geeticka Chauhan (MIT), Brian Tse (Oxford), Mrinmaya Sachan (ETH), Rada Mihalcea (University of Michigan)

    3. Overview of "How Current NLP Researchers Think about NLP4SG" (2021) compiled from survey results (keep updating)

    4. Register for a reading group (Once a week for 8 weeks) to go through NLP4SG papers & questions in a group of NLP researchers! [Time: TBD]

    How can I contribute to NLP4SG?

    1. Join our slack "ACL with Love " => See our #nlp4sg-discussions channel!

    2. Contribute your opinions to our ongoing survey "What is NLP for Social Good?" (Link: bit.ly/nlp4sg-survey)

    3. Participate in various discussions:

    • ACL 2021 Workshop -- NLP for Positive Impact 2021 [Schedule (Aug 5)] 

    • ACL 2021 Meetup Event -- NLP for Social Good Meetup [Zoom link] [Time: TBD]

    • More events to come!
